**I. Background Information & Client Interview** 

**A. Background Information** 

New San Roque is a community within the Municipality of Pili, Camarines Sur. As the basic local government unit, the barangay is tasked with delivering essential services and maintaining accurate population records. However, the current manual approach of using paper files and disconnected spreadsheets often leads to significant inefficiencies, data fragmentation, and operational challenges.

**II. Understanding the Problem Domain** 

**A. System Background and Purpose** 

The system is a **Web-based Population Management System** designed to serve as a centralized hub for all population and household data. Its purpose is to provide a single source of truth for resident and household information, implement robust data validation, support multiple user roles with appropriate access controls, and ensure data security and privacy compliance.

**B. Users and Stakeholders** 

* **Admin**: Full system access, user management, and system configuration.  
* **Staff**: Data entry, resident/household management, and basic reporting.  
* **Viewer**: Read-only access to public reports and statistics.  
* **Stakeholders**: Barangay Officials (Leadership/Committee members), Health Workers, and Residents of New San Roque.

**C. Current Problems or Limitations** 

* **Data Fragmentation:** Information is scattered across multiple sources with no centralized repository.  
* **Data Redundancy:** Duplicate resident records exist due to the lack of a unified database.  
* **Time-Consuming Processes:** Report compilation and data verification take excessive time.  
* **Limited Accessibility:** Information is restricted to physical presence at the barangay office.  
* **Error-Prone Operations:** Manual data entry leads to inconsistencies and inaccuracies.


**III. System Requirements** 

**A. Functional Requirements** 

| Operation  | Description |
| ----- | ----- |
| **Resident Management** | Manage resident records ensuring unique combinations of name/birthdate. Handle multiple classifications (Senior, PWD) and assign residents to single households. Support soft deletion for audit purposes. |
| **Household Management** | Create and manage households (Active, Moved Out, Deceased, Disputed). Ensure every household has at least one member and one adult head of the family. |
| **User Account Management** | Manage user accounts with Role-Based Access Control (Admin, Staff, Viewer). |
| **System Audit** | Log all data modifications (Create, Update, Delete) with user timestamps and change details to maintain a complete audit trail. |
| **Authentication** | Secure login using username and password (hashed with bcrypt) with session timeouts after 30 minutes of inactivity. |

**B. Non-Functional Requirements** 

| Category  | Description |
| ----- | ----- |
| **Data Integrity** | Validation rules: Phone numbers must be 11 digits; birth dates cannot be in the future; address fields are required. |
| **Security (Data Protection)** | SSL/TLS encryption for data in transit; AES-256 encryption for sensitive data at rest; input sanitization to prevent SQL injection and XSS. |
| **Reliability (Backup)** | Mechanisms for daily automated backups, weekly full backups, and off-site backup storage. |
| **Performance** | Database optimization using short codes (ENUMs) for space efficiency (e.g., Gender: M/F, Status: A/I/X) |
| **Usability** | Centralized web-based interface replacing disconnected spreadsheets for better accessibility. |

**C. Objects, Attributes, Methods** 

| Class  | Attributes  | Methods |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **Household** | household\_id, zone\_num, house\_num, address, status, head\_resident\_id | addHousehold(), updateStatus(), assignHead(), getResidents() |
| **Resident** | resident\_id, first\_name, last\_name, birth\_date, gender, civil\_status, education, contact\_num, email, status | registerResident(), updateProfile(), softDelete(), validateUnique() |
| **Staff** | staff\_id, first\_name, last\_name, title, category, picture | addStaff(), updateTitle(), uploadPicture() |
| **Account** | acc\_id, username, password, role, staff\_id | login(), logout(), changePassword(), authenticate() |
| **Audit\_Trail** | audit\_id, record\_type, record\_id, details, change\_type, change\_date, acc\_id | logAction(), viewLogs(), archiveLogs() |

**D. Relationships** 

| Relationship  | Type  | Description |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **Household \- Resident** | 1 to Many | A household contains one or more residents; a resident belongs to exactly one household. |
| **Household \- Head** | 1 to 1 | A household has exactly one Head Resident (linked via head\_resident\_id). |
| **Staff \- Account** | 1 to 0..1 | A staff member may have an associated user account for system access (staff\_id FK in Account). |
| **Account \- Audit** | 1 to Many | An account performs multiple actions that are logged in the audit trail (acc\_id FK in Audit\_Trail). |
